    "comment": "Rationale: The work shows CDH-9 immunofluorescence in the proximity of synaptic processes. Transfected expression of a tagged version of the CDH-9 indicates a discrete localization of the recombinantly expressed product outside but close to synaptic cluster. Overall evidence suggest targeted expression. Figure 8 highlights shRNA knock down of the CDH-9 proteins exerts a disruption of synaptic structure supporting synaptic function of the protein as assessed by quantitative morphometric EM.\n\n3/7/2017 Pim\n- Fig.5C shows the homophilic adhesive property of Cadh9. Experimental description: Mouse in utero poration are explicitly mentioned in the methods but the culture method cited in the supplementary indicates rats and methods and figures do not clarify this.\n\n3/2/2017 Pim\n- Overexpressed protein is of mouse species. Literal \"cDNA encoding the predicted full-length cadherin-9 gene described in GenBank NM_009869.1 was amplified from a P7 mouse hippocampal cDNA library.\"",
